<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy – StillOn" %>

<div class="sms-page">
  <div class="sms-shell">

    <div class="sms-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: March 2026</p>
    </div>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul class="sms-list">
        <li><strong>Organizers:</strong> first name, phone number. That's it — no email, no password.</li>
        <li><strong>Guests:</strong> name and, if you choose to provide it, your phone number for day-of reminders. Both are voluntary beyond your name.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <ul class="sms-list">
        <li>Your phone number is used only to send you SMS messages directly related to hangouts you're involved in — verification codes, RSVP reminders, and day-of reminders.</li>
        <li>We don't use your data for advertising. We don't sell it. We don't share it with third parties except Twilio, our SMS provider, solely to deliver messages.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>If you RSVP with a phone number, we save it in a cookie on your device. This is purely functional — it lets us pre-fill your RSVP form the next time you visit an invite link, so you don't have to type your number again. The cookie expires after one year. No tracking, no analytics.</p>
      <p>You can clear it at any time by clearing your browser cookies, or it will be removed automatically if you RSVP and leave the phone field blank.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>SMS opt-out</h2>
      <p>Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message to unsubscribe. Reply <strong>HELP</strong> for support. Message and data rates may apply. For full details on our SMS program, see the <%= link_to "SMS Program page", sms_info_path %>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>Guest RSVP data (name, phone) is tied to a specific event occurrence and is not used after the event passes. If you'd like your data removed, email us and we'll take care of it.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="sms-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Reach us at <strong>hello@stilon.app</strong>.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>
